5. Ethical & Sensitivity Considerations
Q5a: Demographic disparities - how explicit?
The data shows real disparities (Black households have 1/8th the wealth of white households, pay gaps by race/gender exist). Should we:
- Model realistically (show actual disparities to help users understand systemic challenges)
- Model but contextualize (include educational notes about why disparities exist)
- Make configurable (users can toggle "realistic mode" vs "idealized equal opportunity mode")
Q5b: Negative outcomes and blame?
When showing bankruptcy/incarceration outcomes, should the simulation:
- Frame as systemic/bad luck vs personal choices?
- Include explanatory text about circumstances vs decisions?
- Show "escape paths" from negative states?
My assumption: Model realistically but include context/education, make disparities visible to promote understanding, emphasize both structural factors and individual agency.
Yes, good.
