8. Computational Budget & Realism Tradeoffs
Q8: Realism vs runtime for personal mode?
For a single user running on EPYC cluster:
- Fast mode: 1 profile × 100 strategies × 10 reps × 45 years = ~45K person-years (~5 seconds)
- Balanced mode: 1 profile × 500 strategies × 50 reps × 45 years = ~1.1M person-years (~1 minute)
- Comprehensive mode: 1 profile × 2000 strategies × 200 reps × 45 years = ~18M person-years (~10 minutes)
For research/cohort mode:
- Fast: 1K agents × 10 strategies × 5 reps × 45 years = ~2.25M person-years (~30 seconds)
- Balanced: 10K agents × 20 strategies × 10 reps × 45 years = ~90M person-years (~5 minutes)
- Comprehensive: 100K agents × 50 strategies × 20 reps × 45 years = ~4.5B person-years (~several hours on cluster)
What's your target runtime for interactive use?
- Under 1 minute for quick feedback?
- 5-10 minutes acceptable for comprehensive analysis?
- Hours for research runs (batched, not interactive)?
My assumption: Tiered modes - Fast for iteration (<1 min), Balanced for final decisions (5 min), Comprehensive for research (batch jobs).
We want to emphasize the research, but have options for all due to the fact of this being a research project.
